text: Jean-Paul Hinako Oulaï (born 19 September 1990 in Abidjan, Ivory Coast) is a footballer defender who is last known to have played for Magwe of the Myanmar National League in 2017. ==Career== ===Thailand=== Completed a move to Inter Pattaya, then of the Thai League 3, in 2016.Jean Paul Oulai signe à Inter Pattaya FC de Thaïlande Niarela.net ===Myanmar=== Arriving at Magwe of the Myanmar National League in January 2017,Jean Paul Hinako Oulaï dépose ses valises en Birmanie à Magwe, un club de première division Raildainfo.com Oulaï helped them secure the preseason 2016 MFF Charity Cup, the 6th iteration of the competition.Birmanie: Jean Paul Oulaï vainqueur de la Super Coupe Référence14Sport == References == == External links == * All hope is not lost -Oulai Jean-Paul ( AS Real midfielder) (Archived) * Football365.fr Article * at National-Football-Teams * Thaileague Profile Category:Mali international footballers Category:Malian footballers Category:Association football defenders Category:1990 births Category:Living people Category:Sportspeople from Abidjan Category:Ivorian footballers Category:Ivorian expatriate footballers Category:Expatriate footballers in Myanmar Category:Malian expatriate footballers Category:Expatriate footballers in Thailand Category:Expatriate footballers in Mali Category:Bangkok Christian College F.C. players Category:Magway FC players Category:Myanmar National League players
